---
/** Retainer effort skew: activity reporting vs revenue architecture. */
---
<div class="lp-viz lp-viz--on-dark lp-chart-bars" data-viz>
  <div class="lp-viz-head">
    <p class="lp-viz-kicker">Incentive shape</p>
    <p class="lp-viz-title">What most retainers optimise for</p>
    <p class="lp-viz-note">
      Activity is easy to report. Revenue outcomes are harder — which is exactly why the wrong incentives produce the wrong work.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="lp-viz-bars lp-viz-bars--dark" role="img" aria-label="Long bar for activity dashboards short bar for revenue proof">
    <div class="lp-hbar lp-hbar--dark">
      <span class="lp-hbar-label">Dashboards: posts, reach, cadence</span>
      <div class="lp-hbar-track lp-hbar-track--dark">
        <div class="lp-hbar-fill lp-hbar-fill--ghost" style="--w: 96%"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="lp-hbar lp-hbar--dark">
      <span class="lp-hbar-label">Proof tied to pipeline &amp; close rate</span>
      <div class="lp-hbar-track lp-hbar-track--dark">
        <div class="lp-hbar-fill lp-hbar-fill--accent" style="--w: 34%"></div>
      </div>
      <span class="lp-hbar-cap lp-hbar-cap--light">What we measure against</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
